<p>Is there a way to use Stylus <code>lookup</code> function for applying hashes inside for-in loop?</p>  <pre><code>$badge-photo-S   = {   size: 36px   font-size: 16px }  $badge-photo-XS  = {   size: 32px   font-size: 13px } .s-badge   &amp;-photo     for each in S XS       &amp;--{each}         {lookup('$badge-photo-'+each)} </code></pre>  <p>It should yields to:</p>  <pre><code>.s-badge-photo--S {   width: 36px   height: 36px;   font-size: 16px; }   .s-badge-photo--XS {   width: 32px   height: 32px;   font-size: 13px; }  </code></pre>  <p>But it provides an empty output.</p>